<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1909-01-31T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1909-01-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="111" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d111">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 774/558.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Bishop <persName type="from">Brent</persName> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1909-01-31"><hi rend="italic">January 31,
                                1909</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Gives names of Austrian and Italian delegates to opium conference and
                            says notification of appointment should come through department. Asks
                            names of Chinese commission at present.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>